{"color": "cyan", "emoji": "\ud83d\udee0", "event_type": "Command Finished", "message": "completed, exit 0: /bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba backend/app/ai/prompts/intent_parser.md | sed -n '1,260p'\"", "raw_event": {"item": {"aggregated_output": "     1\tYou are Storyteller's backend-only chat intent parser.\n     2\t\n     3\tYour job is to translate a single user chat message into a structured backend proposal for the bedtime-story workflow.\n     4\t\n     5\tRules:\n     6\t- Return JSON only. Do not wrap it in markdown.\n     7\t- Never invent action types, stages, or extracted fields beyond the allowed catalog.\n     8\t- You may propose zero or more actions, but you must never claim that an action has already been applied.\n     9\t- Use the current stage context and session summary to decide which stage the message is most likely trying to change.\n    10\t- If the message is too vague to turn into a safe proposal, return `status=\"needs_clarification\"`, set `needs_clarification=true`, leave `proposed_actions.actions` empty, explain the ambiguity in `clarification_reason`, and ask one concise follow-up question in `assistant_response`.\n    11\t- Keep `assistant_response` calm, concise, and useful. Prefer one or two sentences.\n    12\t- Respect the default confirmation policy. Any action whose default policy is `confirm_first` must set `requires_confirmation=true`.\n    13\t- Do not use copyrighted-author labels or unsafe bedtime framing.\n    14\t- When the user refers to a specific saved pitch, character sheet, or beat revision, include the strongest available identifier fields instead of leaving the target implicit.\n    15\t- For `refine_character_sheet`, prefer filling `focus_character_names`, `change_summary`, and `change_impact` when the message gives enough signal to do so safely.\n    16\t\n    17\tAllowed action catalog:\n    18\t$action_catalog_json\n    19\t\n    20\tDefault policy by action type:\n    21\t$default_policy_json\n    22\t\n    23\tRelated backend tool registry:\n    24\t$story_tool_catalog_json\n    25\t\n    26\tCurrent stage context:\n    27\t$stage_context_json\n    28\t\n    29\tSession summary:\n    30\t$session_summary\n    31\t\n    32\tUser message:\n    33\t$user_message\n", "command": "/bin/zsh -lc \"nl -ba backend/app/ai/prompts/intent_parser.md | sed -n '1,260p'\"", "exit_code": 0, "id": "item_39", "status": "completed", "type": "command_execution"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 77, "prompt_index": 50, "prompt_name": "49 \u2014 Beat Sheet Refinement UI and Chat Controls", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T00:23:46-07:00"}
